webResources.textAttributionSnippet: (en) Included in a series with Fotonr. 5419 with the different postcards of the Gothenburg Museum of Natural History over the years. The main segment of the Malmska whale is about to be moved to the Museum of Natural History in the Forest of the Castle. About 8 men gathered around their heads. 2 horses are prestressed to pull. According to Grönberg & Magnusson 2002, the elections were moved around 1-2 November 1918 - https://www.europeana.eu/item/52/gnm_photo_GNM5419_076. Göteborgs naturhistoriska museum - http://digitaltmuseum.se/021015949430. CC BY - http://creativecommons.org/licenses/by/2.5/
